race.comment: TULONG (4) has been freshened up since his last start, third at Ipswich just over 6 weeks ago. He has been close up in a trial since then, and will don the blinkers for the first time. A 2kg claim will help, and in an easier field, he can get the job done this time. HEROIC DELANEYS (8) has been improving in each of her 3 starts to date. She is nicely placed over 1400m and can get the job done this time. CONCADOR (2) battled away fairly well for sixth over 2000m at Toowoomba 13 days ago, and will be rock-hard fit for the drop back to 1400m. He cops a wide gate, but can run into the top 4 placings. Watch for him late. PRINCE OF SYNERGY (3) ran a much better race for second here nearly 3 weeks ago, when beaten by a nose. He has a superior gate this time and can go one better. EXODINI (6) did not do much on debut at Ballina a fortnight ago, but he has the pole position this time, and can finish a lot closer. Include in all combinations.
